Paul,<br><br>
I sometimes have some meloncoly times, but many here have helped; Ed and Art especially.  <br><br>
I don't have any daughters, and I swear (actually do sometimes) that I haven't figured women out yet and may never.  But emotion is just that--usually it isn't the real person's thoughts, just some short-circuits talking.  I've tried this:<br><br>
--Never go to bed angry.<br>
--Don't look back.<br><br>
Many times we try living like a driver who's steering by looking in the rear-view mirror.  We dwell in the past, and cannot therefore see what's coming at us.  If we can concentrate of the present and the future, then we can make use of past experiences to guide us along the pathway.  But if we concentrate only on the past, we are doomed to hid the obsticles in our future path.<br><br>
'Hope this helps.  Enjoy!
